[TASK] Generate lockfile via Actions, commit it, and restore `npm ci`
[WHEN] Now — Sun 14 Sep 2025, 14:22 (Europe/London)
[HOST] Adaptive
[CONFIRM] Gemini: Acknowledge and log.

1) Create .github/workflows/generate-lockfile.yml with:
---
name: Generate Lockfile
on:
  workflow_dispatch:
jobs:
  lockfile:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: actions/setup-node@v4
        with: { node-version: '20' }
      - run: npm install --no-audit --no-fund
      - name: Commit lockfile
        env:
          GH_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}
        run: |
          if [ -f package-lock.json ]; then
            git config user.name "github-actions[bot]"
            git config user.email "41898282+github-actions[bot]@users.noreply.github.com"
            git add package-lock.json
            git commit -m "build: add package-lock.json"
            git push
          fi
---

2) Trigger this workflow manually (Actions → Generate Lockfile → Run workflow).
3) Create a branch `chore/ci-restore-npm-ci`, edit .github/workflows/ci.yml → replace all
   `npm install --no-audit --no-fund` with `npm ci`.
4) Open PR:
   Title: chore(ci): restore `npm ci` with lockfile
   Body: Add deterministic installs now that package-lock.json exists.
   Enable Auto-merge (squash).

OUTPUT → ACCESS CARD: PR link + checks.
